# Code Style & TypeScript

## TypeScript

- `strict: true` — never disable; `target: ES2020`, `module: commonjs`, output to `dist/`
- Controllers always return `Promise<void>`
- Use `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions only
- No `any` — use `unknown` + type guards; no `!` without proof — prefer `?.`
- Guard pg `rowCount`: `if (result.rowCount && result.rowCount > 0)`
- All I/O: `async/await` — no callbacks or `.then()`
- Exception: BullMQ `.add()` is fire-and-forget

## Naming Conventions

| Token | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| TS files | dot-separated kebab | `ticket.service.ts` |
| SQL files | kebab-case | `schema.sql` |
| Variables / Functions | camelCase | `getUserById` |
| Interfaces | PascalCase — no `I`-prefix | `TicketRow` |
| Constants | SCREAMING_SNAKE | `SALT_ROUNDS` |
| Env variables | SCREAMING_SNAKE | `PG_DATABASE` |
| PG columns/tables/ENUMs | snake_case | `created_at`, `ticket_status` |
| Redis keys | `{resource}:{id}` | `ticket:uuid-123` |

## Exports

| Layer | Style |
|---|---|
| Router, App, Middleware, Config | `export default` |
| Controllers, Services, Utils, DB helpers | Named exports |

Never mix both styles in one file.

## Imports

Group in this order: built-ins → third-party → internal.
Use `* as` for services; destructure for types.

## Zod Validation

All schemas in `src/modules/{module}/{module}.schemas.ts`.

```ts
import { z } from 'zod';

export const createTicketSchema = z.object({
  title:       z.string().trim().min(1).max(500),
  description: z.string().trim().min(1),
  priority:    z.enum(['LOW', 'MEDIUM', 'HIGH', 'URGENT']).default('MEDIUM'),
});

export const listTicketsQuerySchema = z.object({
  status: z.enum(['OPEN', 'IN_PROGRESS', 'RESOLVED', 'CLOSED', 'CANCELLED']).optional(),
  page:   z.coerce.number().int().min(1).default(1),   // coerce required for query strings
  limit:  z.coerce.number().int().min(1).max(100).default(20),
});

export type CreateTicketPayload = z.infer<typeof createTicketSchema>;
```

### Rules

- `z.coerce.number()` for all numeric query params — never `parseInt`
- `.trim().min(1)` on all string inputs — rejects whitespace-only
- `.default()` on optional fields — services never receive `undefined`
- `z.infer<typeof schema>` for types — never define separately from schemas
- `safeParse` in middleware; `.parse()` for path params only (throws ZodError → errorHandler → 400)

### Path Parameters

```ts
export const uuidParam = z.string().uuid({ message: 'Invalid UUID' });
// In controller: const id = uuidParam.parse(req.params.id);
```

## Error Handling

- Controllers: `try/catch` → `next(err)` in catch — never `res.status(5xx).json()`
- Services: throw with `statusCode` for domain errors (`400`, `403`, `404`, `409`)
- Always `return` after `error(res, ...)` to prevent double-send

```ts
// Controller pattern
export const getTicket = async (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction): Promise<void> => {
  try {
    const id = uuidParam.parse(req.params.id);
    const ticket = await ticketService.getById(id);
    success(res, ticket);
  } catch (err) {
    next(err);
  }
};
```

## Comments

Only when the **why** is non-obvious. Never describe what the code does — no narration comments.

## Formatting & Linting

- **Prettier:** `singleQuote: true`, `semi: true`, `trailingComma: all`, `printWidth: 100`, `tabWidth: 2`
- **ESLint:** `no-unused-vars` error (prefix unused with `_`), `no-explicit-any` warn
- Run: `npm run lint:fix` / `npm run format`
- Husky pre-commit hook runs lint-staged — never use `--no-verify`
